{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      vCluster — Virtual K8s inside the main cluster\n      Runs a full K8s API server as a pod inside your existing cluster. Looks and behaves like a real cluster from the outside, but shares the underlying nodes.\n      RAM overhead: ~200–400MB per vCluster\n      How: Deploy via Helm into a test namespace. Point your kubeconfig at it. Tear down and recreate in seconds.\n      \n        ProsFull API isolation (own namespaces, RBAC, CRDs)Near-zero extra RAMEphemeral — perfect for CI/test teardownsAlready supported by Helm (which we're deploying anyway)\n        ConsShares worker node resources — noisy neighbour possibleSome cluster-level resources aren't fully isolated (nodes, storage classes)","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1774519340937}
